        <section>
            <h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>
       <ul>
                <li>Spring (March to May) offers blooming parks and mild weather.</li>
                <li>Autumn (September to November) has fewer crowds and pleasant temperatures.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Transportation</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Use the Underground (Tube) for fast travel across the city.</li>
                <li>London buses are convenient and scenic.</li>
                <li>Rent bikes using Santander Cycles for short trips.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Accommodation</h2>
             <ul>
                <li>Luxury hotels are available in the West End and Kensington.</li>
                <li>Budget options like hostels and guesthouses are in areas like Camden or Shoreditch.</li>
                <li>Book early during peak seasons.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Local Tips</h2>
           ul>
                <li>Get an Oyster card or contactless payment for cheaper travel.</li>
                <li>Many top museums are free to enter.</li>
                <li>Avoid peak hours (7-9 AM and 5-7 PM) when using public transport.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
